        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/textViewlessonsix10"
            android:layout_width="360dp"
            android:layout_height="400dp"
            android:text="A little fire safety maintenance can go a long way towards reducing your risk of a fire at home. Here are some fire prevention tips you can do to help lower your risk of a fire breaking out:\n
- Practice home fire drills regularly and make them realistic. Have different escape routes blocked and practice using alternate exits.\n
- Lint build-up in your dryer’s vent can cause a fire. Get rid of it before it becomes a problem using a Dryer Maintenance Kit that includes a vent brush, lint trap brush, and vacuum attachment.\n
- Make it a habit to unplug all countertop appliances when they aren’t being used.\n
- Install a carbon monoxide detector.\n
- Store cigarette lighters and matches where children can’t get them.\n
- Don’t use an outdoor grill or charcoal grill indoors or on a porch or balcony.\n
- Test your smoke alarm regularly to make sure it’s in working condition.\n
- Change battery-operated smoke detector batteries once each year.\n
"
            app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
            app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
            app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@+id/imageViewlessonsixsixth" />

